<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,678,847]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,678,703]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Comments.</emphasis>
Males of 
<emphasis box="[401,563,678,703]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Syntrichomyia</emphasis>
are easily recognized by the fusion between the gonocoxites and hypandrium forming a plate-like sclerite, the posterolateral surface of which has bristles inserted; other charactersitics include the basal fusion of gonostyli with divergent apices lightly sclerotized and the hypoproct bilobed. Subgenus 
<emphasis box="[151,313,786,811]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Syntrichomyia</emphasis>
was proposed for grouping three species from 
<collectingCountry box="[840,908,786,811]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and one from 
<collectingCountry box="[1071,1163,787,811]" name="Panama" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Panamá</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
